{
  "text": "To keep the queue of user k stable, we must have \u03c1 k < 1 or f (\u03b3 k ) > \u03bb k \u03c4 k . Now, let W k be a random variable representing the total packet delay for user k. This delay includes the time the packet spends in the queue as well as the service time. It can be shown that, for the M/G/1 queue considered here, the average wait time (including the queuing and service time) for user k is given by (see [CITATION_1] )",
